  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A prospective pilot study to evaluate the recanalization and safety of mechanical
      thrombectomy through a cerebral angiogram in patients with stroke symptoms last seen normal
      between 8 - 24 hours.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Ischemic stroke patients who are 8-24 hrs from symptom onset without prior mechanical or IV
      thrombolytic treatment and are screen with CT or MR perfusion imaging showing penumbra and
      infarction not &gt; 1/3rd the territory.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
